		<td><b>Re: feasibility of having a game editor run on the SNES itse</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A tile editor that runs on the Super NES allows previewing in real time what composite encoding artifacts will do to your tiles. Otherwise, you have to have the computer, its monitor, the Super NES Control Deck, and its monitor all in the same room, with some sort of serial cable between the two.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


